    "Do not treat parent verification or planning review as implementation approval."
  ],
  "tasks": [
    "Invoke the ordered required skills, replay subject admission exactly, and return BLOCKED if any subject byte/count differs.",
    "Review tests before implementation and report findings in Critical, Required, Optional, Nit order.",
    "Audit the closed eight-field record, duplicate-safe YAML admission, exact serializer and renderer, independent fingerprint domains, bounds, and failure precedence.",
    "Audit trusted no-follow reads, final identity/byte stability, atomic Unix mutation ordering, non-Unix pre-mutation refusal, and absence of legacy Markdown influence.",
    "Audit descriptor-selected path ownership from engine through flow/compiler/CLI, fixed-sibling ownership adaptation, unchanged C03 fingerprint inputs, and exact C04 .2 transition.",
    "Audit Environment Inventory reference-only cutover, setup non-authoring behavior, doctor 1.1.0 nullable fingerprint row, flow bridge domains/logging/sections/budget behavior, and HCM-2.4 deletion lifetime.",
    "Audit API compatibility, error disclosure, denial-of-service bounds, data integrity, deterministic ordering, dead code, and unbounded allocation or repeated parse/render work.",
    "Assess verification: focused Windows and WSL suites passed; WSL Clippy -D warnings, rustfmt, git diff --check, and cargo doc passed; broad mounted-worktree CLI result is 87 passed/16 CRLF-only failures; Windows strict success remains intentionally impossible while native Windows refusal/no-mutation tests pass.",
